translated:
Sigrfrid, director, Gothenburg, b. Vmm in Vicklelby, Kalm. 1st marriage 20 with Harriet Price. - Graduation from Schartau's Trade Institute in 1911. Employment at Margarin A-B Svea in Kalmar from 1913-1922, department head at A-B Pellerins Margarine Factory in Gothenburg from 1922-1926, executive director there since 1927, and also for Margarin A-B Zenith in Malmö since 1931. Member of the board for Margarine Factory Sales A-B, Gothenburg Biscuit Factory A-B, A-B Mill Interests, and others. 

Hilly, principal, Jönköping, b. 30/10/1900 in Jönköping, son of master mechanic S. R. W. and his wife Johansson. - Completed 8th grade at a public school with normal school curriculum in 1918, completed household economics vocational school in 1924. Studied in England from 1920-1921, in Germany from 1921-1922, 1934, 1935, and 1939, and in France in 1947. Employed as a school kitchen teacher at Jönköping Western Girls' School and Jönköping Eastern Girls' School, principal at Jönköping City Vocational School from 1933. Member of the central board for the Swedish School Kitchen Teachers Association, the pension committee, the home help committee, chairperson of the Professional Women's Club. Member of the city council from 1942-1946.
